Product of tour operation. The concept of package tour. Working as a tour operator - laws and regulations. Client profile and changes in the client's wishes and needs. Components of a package. Negotiations with the principles and sponsors. Risk management. Cost accounting and pricing in tour operation. Variable costs and fixed costs. Terminology of tour operating in Estonian and English.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides knowledge of the principles of tour operation, knowledge and skills to plan a travel package based on the client's expectations, research and teamwork skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) is able to explain the principles and processes of tour operating; 2) is able to analyze socio-cultural, economic and ecological impact of events on a destination; 3) plans and compiles a package based on client's expectations; 4) calculates the price of the package; 5) uses appropriate vocabulary.
